<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-430-707  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 430 707.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 31 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NIST seeks GOSIP testing facilities. (National Institute ofStandards and Technology, Government Open Systems InterconnectionProfile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. National Institute of Standards and TechnologyGovernment Open Systems Interconnection Profile (Computer networkprotocol)StandardsTestingTest EquipmentGovernment ContractsCompetitive Bidding.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NIST SEEKS GOSIP TESTING FACILITIES WASHINGTON, DC, U.S.A., 1990 JULY 23 (NB)-- The National Institute of Standards and Testing (NIST, formerly the Bureauof Standards) has announced that it is soliciting test systems needed toestablish a testing program to ensure that products meet the Government OpenSystems Interconnection Profile (GOSIP) Federal Information ProcessingStandard 146.andM;Applications for listing of qualified test systems and accreditedlaboratories (to be published by NIST this fall) can be obtained by writingto Stephen Nightingale, GOSIP Testing Program, B141 Technology Bldg., NIST,Gaithersburg, Md.andP;  20899 or calling him at 301-975-3616 or 3665.andM;After August 15, 1990, all federal agencies must purchase network systemsthat conform to the GOSIP standard.andM;(John McCormick/1990727/Press Contact: Jan Kosko, NIST, 301-975- 2762)</TEXT></DOC>